<li id="cite_note-21"><b><a href="#cite_ref-21" title="">^</a></b> Neither Chao nor Lin, however, followed this practice.</li>
<li id="cite_note-22"><b><a href="#cite_ref-22" title="">^</a></b> For an account of the phonetization of Chinese in Taiwan, see Chen(1999):189</li>
<li id="cite_note-23"><b><a href="#cite_ref-23" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFWi-vun_Taiffalo_Chiung">Wi-vun Taiffalo Chiung. <a href="http://www.de-han.org/pehoeji/lomaji/4.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.de-han.org/pehoeji/lomaji/4.htm" rel="nofollow">"Romanization and Language Planning in Taiwan"</a>. Center for Thoat-Han Studies<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.de-han.org/pehoeji/lomaji/4.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.de-han.org/pehoeji/lomaji/4.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.de-han.org/pehoeji/lomaji/4.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-02-27</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Romanization+and+Language+Planning+in+Taiwan&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Wi-vun+Taiffalo+Chiung&amp;rft.au=Wi-vun+Taiffalo+Chiung&amp;rft.pub=Center+for+Thoat-Han+Studies&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.de-han.org%2Fpehoeji%2Flomaji%2F4.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Gwoyeu_Romatzyh"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> This is an online version of Chiung(2001).</li>
<li id="cite_note-24"><b><a href="#cite_ref-24" title="">^</a></b> See Chao(1948):19–24 and Chao(1968a):20–25 for tables and fuller discussion. Complete tables of GR initials and finals are also given in the <a href="/wiki/Spelling_in_Gwoyeu_Romatzyh#Basic_forms" title="Spelling in Gwoyeu Romatzyh">main article</a>.</li>
